# mailpouch — Environment Variable Reference
#
# NOTE: Credentials and connection settings live in ~/.mailpouch.json
# (mode 0600), managed via the settings UI (`npx mailpouch-settings`).
# They are NOT loaded from environment variables, on purpose, to avoid
# accidental exposure to other processes.
#
# The variables below are advanced/optional overrides only. Copy this file
# to .env if you need any of them; leave it unset otherwise.

# ── Optional path overrides ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# MAILPOUCH_CONFIG=~/.mailpouch.json
# MAILPOUCH_SCHEDULER_STORE=~/.mailpouch-scheduled.json
# MAILPOUCH_LOG_FILE=~/.mailpouch.log
# MAILPOUCH_PENDING=~/.mailpouch.pending.json
# MAILPOUCH_AUDIT=~/.mailpouch.audit.jsonl

# ── Per-launch behavior ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MAILPOUCH_INSECURE_BRIDGE=1   # opt into localhost Bridge w/o pinned cert
# MAILPOUCH_TIER=complete       # core / extended / complete
# PORT=8765                     # settings UI HTTP server port

# Legacy PM_BRIDGE_MCP_* (v2.1) and PROTONMAIL_MCP_* (original) names are
# still honored through v3.0.0 (silent aliases). New installs should use
# the MAILPOUCH_* forms above. Precedence if multiple are set:
# MAILPOUCH_* > PM_BRIDGE_MCP_* > PROTONMAIL_MCP_*.
